14th Annual
1994 Rochester Forth Conference
on
Rapid Prototyping

June 22 - 25, 1994
University of Rochester

Call for Papers

The 1994 Rochester Forth Conference on Rapid Prototyping will be held at the
University of Rochester June 22 - 25th.   Rapid prototyping refers to techniques
to allow rapid project turnaround using software and/or hardware.   Forth
technology is especially well adapted to supporting such systems.  Forth
provides an interactive, extensible, incremental compiler.  Forth is used in
applications ranging from spacecraft control to medical imaging,
telecommunications to financial software.

With the recent acceptance by the IEEE of the Open Firmware Standard 1275, which
is a tokenized Forth, and the acceptance by ANSI (American National Standards
Institute) of the X3.215-1994 ANS Forth Standard, this technology is taking on
growing importance.  Currently the Open Firmware predecessor to IEEE 1275, known
as Open Boot, is used by Sun Microsystems, and those companies making SPARC
machines or boards to be used with them.  APPLE and  IBM have indicated they
will use it on future on PowerPC platforms.

Other areas of interest at the Conference include Forth under Windows, Forth vs
C and C++, object oriented programming, embedded systems, real time systems, and
Forth with other languages.  Those wishing to present a paper should submit a
100 word abstract by June 1st and a final 5 page paper by June 21st.  Type
should be no smaller than 8 point.  Author's guidelines will be sent.  Longer
papers will be considered for submission to the refereed Journal of Forth
Application and Research.

The Conference will be preceeded by a 1 day ANS Forth Standards Committee
meeting, on Tuesday, June 21st to which Conference attendees are invited to
attend.  Wednesday morning will have a review of the ANS process, the Forth
Standard, and proposed compliance followed by the Conference program beginning
Wednesday afternoon.  Sessions will continue on Thursday and Friday, with a
vendors day open to the public on Saturday, June 25th.

