Brenda, Alex and I look forward to seeing you all in Rochester again this year!

There is an extra significance to this year's Conference.  The 1981 Rochester
Forth Conference on Forth Standards was one of the starting points for what
became the 83-Forth Standard, which was a starting point for the ANS Forth
effort.  The Institute for Applied Forth Research, Inc. participated in the ANS
Forth Standard for much of its duration, hosting two meetings at the University
of Rochester.  With the recent acceptance of the ANS Forth Standard and the
final meeting of the ANS Forth Technical Committee, the effort comes full circle
once again in Rochester.  We welcome, and praise, all of those who participated
in this long and distinguished effort.
